## Troubleshooting

### Quick Diagnostic Commands

```bash
# 1. Check installation
ls -la "/Library/Application Support/Adobe/CEP/extensions/com.splice.panel/"

# 2. Verify files
find "/Library/Application Support/Adobe/CEP/extensions/com.splice.panel/" -name "*.js" | wc -l
# Should show: 16 JavaScript files

# 3. Test backend
curl -I https://splice-api-production.up.railway.app/health
# Should return: HTTP/2 200

# 4. Enable debug mode
defaults write com.adobe.CSXS.12 PlayerDebugMode 1

# 5. Check logs (Chrome Remote Debugger)
open http://localhost:8092/
# Click "SPLICE" ‚Üí Console tab
```

### Common Issues

**1. Panel Not Appearing**
- Solution: Enable debug mode (see above)
- Restart Premiere Pro
- Check Premiere version (must be 23.0+)

**2. Blank White Screen**
- Solution: Open Chrome debugger (localhost:8092)
- Check console for JavaScript errors
- Reinstall if critical errors found

**3. GO Button Does Nothing**
- Solution: Run diagnostics (Debug button)
- Verify sequence is active (not just open)
- Check backend connectivity

**4. Authentication Fails**
- Solution: Clear localStorage (Chrome debugger)
- Check internet connection
- Verify backend CSRF endpoint responds

**5. AI Features Timeout**
- Solution: Try shorter clip (1-2 min) first
- Check credit balance
- Verify backend health endpoint

